SIMPLE: anomalistical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anomalistical
<hw>A*nom`a*lis"tic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>anomalistique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Irregular; departing from common or established rules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the anomaly, or
angular distance of a planet from its perihelion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Anomalistic month</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Month</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Anomalistic revolution</b></col>,
<cd>the period in which a planet or satellite goes through the complete
cycles of its changes of anomaly, or from any point in its elliptic
orbit to the same again.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Anomalistic</b></col>, or
<col><b>Periodical year</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See under
<er>Year</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anomalistically</ent>⟦br⟧
